015/hju20.mp3", "start_seconds": 152.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2015-02-11T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2015/hju20.mp3", "start_seconds": 152.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2015-02-11T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2015/hju20.mp3", "start_seconds": 152.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2015-02-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2015/hou23.mp3", "start_seconds": 6390.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2015-02-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2015/hou23.mp3", "start_seconds": 6390.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2015-02-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2015/hou23.mp3", "start_seconds": 6390.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2015-03-03T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2015/sju30.mp3", "start_seconds": 1485.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2015-03-03T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2015/sju30.mp3", "start_seconds": 1485.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2015-03-03T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2015/sju30.mp3", "start_seconds": 1485.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2015-03-03T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2015/sju30.mp3", "start_seconds": 1485.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 6515, "bill_version_id": 33548, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2015-01-23T09:56:04.757-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow a law enforcement officer to issue a citation without a notary. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 23-1A be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: It is sufficient if a law enforcement officer, in lieu of verification under oath, signs the following statement printed or written on a complaint or summons for a Class 2 misdemeanor or a petty offense \"I declare and affirm under the penalties of perjury that this complaint or summons has been examined by me, and to the best of my knowledge and belief, is in all things true and correct.\" Any person who signs this statement as provided for in this section, knowing the statement to be false or untrue, in whole or in part, is guilty of perjury. 170 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.098 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 6515, "bill_version_id": 34901, "bill_version": "House Judiciary Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2015-02-11T13:52:10.747-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow a law enforcement officer to issue a citation without a notary. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 23-1A-5 be amended to read as follows: 23-1A-5. Any person may sign a petty offense complaint for an offense which occurred in his presence. A petty offense complaint, other than one issued by a law enforcement officer, shall be signed under oath. It is sufficient if a law enforcement officer, in lieu of signing the petty offense complaint under oath, signs the following statement printed or written on a complaint or summons for a petty offense on a uniform traffic ticket: \"I declare and affirm under the penalties of perjury that this complaint or summons has been examined by me, and to the best of my knowledge and belief, is in all things true and correct.\" Any person who signs this statement as provided for in this section, knowing the statement to be false or untrue, in whole or in part, is guilty of perjury. Section 2. That \u00a7 23A-2-1 be amended to read as follows: 23A-2-1. A complaint is a written statement of the essential facts constituting an offense charged. It must be signed under oath before a person authorized to administer oaths in the State of South Dakota. It is sufficient if a law enforcement officer, in lieu of signing a complaint for a Class 2 misdemeanor under oath, signs the following statement printed or written on a complaint or summons on a uniform traffic ticket: \"I declare and affirm under the penalties of perjury that this complaint or summons has been examined by me, and to the best of my knowledge and belief, is in all things true and correct.\" Any person who signs this statement as provided for in this section, knowing the statement to be false or untrue, in whole or in part, is guilty of perjury."}, {"bill_id": 6515, "bill_version_id": 35990, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2015-03-05T09:11:16.17-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 6515, "action_date": "2015-01-23T13:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 33597, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/33597.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 123, "committee_id_action": 286, "committee_id_assigned": 282, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 6515, "action_date": "2015-01-28T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 33680, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/33680.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for hearing", "journal_page": 0, "committee_id_action": 282, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 6515, "action_date": "2015-01-28T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 33995, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/33995.pdf", "status_text": "Deferred to another day", "journal_page": 0, "committee_id_action": 282, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 6515, "action_date": "2015-02-11T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 34728, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/34728.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for hearing", "journal_page": 0, "commit